,"lifeSummary":"當Adriane Jansdr van den Beemden於1500年出生在荷蘭努-布拉班特布雷達時，她的父親Jan Willems Vanden Breemden25歲，母親Maria Adriaen Henric Eements Heems20歲。她於1526年與Jan Mathijsz Peter Dirven結婚。他們至少是3個兒子和3個女兒的父母。她去世於1560年在她的家鄉享年60歲。"},"zh-hans":{"1500–1560":"1500年–1560年","1490–1555":"1490年–1555年","1516–1591":"1516年–1591年","1533–Male":"1533年–殁","1535–Male":"1535年–殁","1537–Female":"1537年–殁","1542–Male":"1542年–殁","1475–Male":"1475年–殁","1480–Female":"1480年–殁","1560":"1560年","1591":"1591年","1480":"1480年","1490":"1490年","1535":"1535年","1500":"1500年","1533":"1533年","1555":"1555年","1542":"1542年","1475":"1475年","1506":"1506年","1516":"1516年","1526":"1526年","1537":"1537年","Breda, Breda, Noord-Brabant, Pays-Bas":"荷兰努-布拉班特布雷達","Netherlands":"荷兰","Poortugaal, South Holland, Netherlands":"荷兰-拉藍德普爾圖加阿爾","Breda, North Brabant, Netherlands":"荷兰努-布拉班特布雷達","lifeSummary":"当Adriane Jansdr van den Beemden于1500年出生在荷兰努-布拉班特布雷達时，她的父亲Jan Willems Vanden Breemden25岁，母亲Maria Adriaen Henric Eements Heems20岁。她于1526年与Jan Mathijsz Peter Dirven结婚。他们至少是3个儿子和3个女儿的父母。她去世于1560年在她的家乡享年60岁。"},"hr":{"1500–1560":"1500.–1560.","1490–1555":"1490–1555.","1516–1591":"1516.–1591","1533–Male":"1533.–preminuo","1535–Male":"1535.–preminuo","1537–Female":"1537.–preminula","1542–Male":"1542.–preminuo","1475–Male":"1475–preminuo","1480–Female":"1480–preminula","1560":"1560.","1591":"1591","1480":"1480","1490":"1490","1535":"1535.","1500":"1500.","1533":"1533.","1555":"1555.","1542":"1542.","1475":"1475","1506":"1506","1516":"1516.","1526":"1526.","1537":"1537.","Breda, Breda, Noord-Brabant, Pays-Bas":"Breda, Noord-Brabant, Nizozemska","Netherlands":"Nizozemska","Poortugaal, South Holland, Netherlands":"Poortugaal, Zuid-Holland, Nizozemska","Breda, North Brabant, Netherlands":"Breda, Noord-Brabant, Nizozemska"},"cs":{"1500–1560":"1500–1560","1490–1555":"1490–1555","1516–1591":"1516–1591","1533–Male":"1533–Zesnulý","1535–Male":"1535–Zesnulý","1537–Female":"1537–Zesnulá","1542–Male":"1542–Zesnulý","1475–Male":"1475–Zesnulý","1480–Female":"1480–Zesnulá","1560":"1560","1591":"1591","1480":"1480","1490":"1490","1535":"1535","1500":"1500","1533":"1533","1555":"1555","1542":"1542","1475":"1475","1506":"1506","1516":"1516","1526":"1526","1537":"1537","Breda, Breda, Noord-Brabant, Pays-Bas":"Breda, Noord-Brabant, Nizozemsko","Netherlands":"Nizozemsko","Poortugaal, South Holland, Netherlands":"Poortugaal, Zuid-Holland, Nizozemsko","Breda, North Brabant, Netherlands":"Breda, Noord-Brabant, Nizozemsko"},"da":{"1500–1560":"1500–1560","1490–1555":"1490–1555","1516–1591":"1516–1591","1533–Male":"1533–Afdød","1535–Male":"1535–Afdød","1537–Female":"1537–Afdød","1542–Male":"1542–Afdød","1475–Male":"1475–Afdød","1480–Female":"1480–Afdød","1560":"1560","1591":"1591","1480":"1480","1490":"1490","1535":"1535","1500":"1500","1533":"1533","1555":"1555","1542":"1542","1475":"1475","1506":"1506","1516":"1516","1526":"1526","1537":"1537","Breda, Breda, Noord-Brabant, Pays-Bas":"Breda, Noord-Brabant, Nederlandene","Netherlands":"Nederlandene","Poortugaal, South Holland, Netherlands":"Poortugaal, Zuid-Holland, Nederlandene","Breda, North Brabant, Netherlands":"Breda, Noord-Brabant, Nederlandene"},"nl":{"1500–1560":"1500–1560","1490–1555":"1490–1555","1516–1591":"1516–1591","1533–Male":"1533–Overleden","1535–Male":"1535–Overleden","1537–Female":"1537–Overleden","1542–Male":"1542–Overleden","1475–Male":"1475–Overleden","1480–Female":"1480–Overleden","1560":"1560","1591":"1591","1480":"1480","1490":"1490","1535":"1535","1500":"1500","1533":"1533","1555":"1555","1542":"1542","1475":"1475","1506":"1506","1516":"1516","1526":"1526","1537":"1537","Breda, Breda, Noord-Brabant, Pays-Bas":"Breda, Noord-Brabant, Nederland","Netherlands":"Nederland","Poortugaal, South Holland, Netherlands":"Poortugaal, Zuid-Holland, Nederland","Breda, North Brabant, Netherlands":"Breda, Noord-Brabant, Nederland"},"en":{"1500–1560":"1500–1560","1490–1555":"1490–1555","1516–1591":"1516–1591","1533–Male":"1533–Deceased","1535–Male":"1535–Deceased","1537–Female":"1537–Deceased","1542–Male":"1542–Deceased","1475–Male":"1475–Deceased","1480–Female":"1480–Deceased","1560":"1560","1591":"1591","1480":"1480","1490":"1490","1535":"1535","1500":"1500","1533":"1533","1555":"1555","1542":"1542","1475":"1475","1506":"1506","1516":"1516","1526":"1526","1537":"1537","Breda, Breda, Noord-Brabant, Pays-Bas":"Breda, North Brabant, Netherlands","Netherlands":"Netherlands","Poortugaal, South Holland, Netherlands":"Poortugaal, South Holland, Netherlands","Breda, North Brabant, Netherlands":"Breda, North Brabant, Netherlands","nameMeanings":[{"name":"van","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Vietnamese Anh, Thanh, Hung, Minh, Vinh, Dung, Hue, Huong, Lan, Quang, Tan, Thuy, Hong, Chi, Hang, Ho, Pok, Sang, Bai, Chin, Ching, Chu, Chuan, Dong.","Vietnamese (<b>Vạn</b>): from the Chinese surname 萬, see   Wan   1.","Vietnamese (<b>Văn</b>): from the Chinese surnames 文 or 聞, see   Wen   2 and 3, and also 5 below."],"variants":[{"name":"Wan","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese Hong, Yi, Qi, Qiang, Wai, Yiu, Yuk, Chien-Min, Fang, Hin, Jichun, Li, Man, Chung, Min, Yiping, Pak, Sik, Sung Man.  Vietnamese Tin, Bang, Da, Hien, Hoi, Lan, Minh Quang, Sau, Tich, Tung, Yaping, Yuet.","Chinese: Mandarin form of the surname 萬, which means ‘ten thousand’ literally or ‘very great number’ figuratively: (i) from the personal name of Bi Wan (畢萬), an official in the state of Jin (located in present-day Shanxi province). He was said to be a descendant of Bi Gong Gao (known as Duke of Bi), the 15th son of the virtuous King Wen of Zhou (reined 1152–1056  BC ). Bi Wan was later granted the fiefdom of Wei (魏), which in 403  BC  became the state of Wei (located in present-day Shanxi, Shaanxi, Henan and Hebei provinces). Some of his descendants adopted Wei (魏) as their surname, while others inherited 萬 (Wan), his personal name, as their surname. (ii) from the personal name Wan (萬), style name of Rui Bo (芮伯, the Earl of Rui), an official of the Western Zhou dynasty (1046–771  BC ), who was granted the fief Rui (located in Ruicheng in Shaanxi province). Some of his descendants inherited Rui (芮), the name of the fief, as their surname, while others inherited 萬 (Wan), his style name, as their surname. (iii) from the placename Wan (萬), the name of a fief (located in Juxian in Shandong province) granted during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ) to an official in the ancient state of Chu. (iv) from the first element of the name of the Wan Si (萬俟) family, who lived in the downstream areas of the Yellow River during the Northern Qi dynasty (550–577  AD ). (v) from the second element of the name of the Tu Wan (吐萬) family, who are members of the Xianbei ethnic group in northern China.","Chinese: Mandarin form of the surname 完, meaning ‘complete’ in Chinese: (i) said to be borne by the descendants of Huan Zhui, a grandson of the Duke Huan of Song (ruler of the state of Song, died 651  BC ). (ii) from Wan (完), the name of Qu Wan (屈完), an official in the state of Chu during the Spring and Autumn Period (770–476  BC ). (iii) shortened form of the compound surname Wan-Yan (完顔), a surname from minority ethnic groups such as Juchen ethnic group in ancient northern China."]}]},{"name":"den","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Chinese: variant Romanization of the surname 鄧, see   Deng  .","Chinese: possibly from the Romanization of certain Chinese personal names of some early Chinese immigrants in the US.","Origin undetermined. — Note: It is possible that in the population figure published by the US Census Bureau the Dutch case-inflected definite article <i>de</i> ‘the’, which forms first part of surnames such as   Den Bleyker   and   Den Boer  , is in some instances counted as an independent surname. Compare   Ten  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Deng","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese Hong, Hua, Jian, Jing, Wei, Wen, Yi, Ying, Chao, Fang, Gang, Hui, Min.","Chinese: Mandarin form of the surname 鄧: (i) from Deng (鄧), the name of a state (located in Dengxian in Henan province) granted to Man Ji, uncle of Wu Ding (a king of the Shang dynasty (1600 –1046  BC )). (ii) from Deng Bowen (鄧伯溫), head of an ancient state (located in present-day Shandong province) dating back to the reign of the legendary Huang Di, the ‘Yellow Emperor’ (<i>c.</i> 27th century  BC ). (iii) from Deng (鄧), a fief (located in Hubei province) granted to descendants of Zhong Kang, the 4th king of the Xia dynasty (2070–1600  BC ). (iv) from Deng Cheng (鄧城, City of Deng), a town in the state of Cai (located in present-day Henan province) during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ). (v) from Deng (鄧), a title of Li Tianyi, the 8th son of Li Yu (the last king of the state of Southern Tang (937–975  AD ) during the Five Dynasties and Ten Kingdoms (907–960) periods). The state of Southern Tang was annexed by Emperor Taizong of Song (939–997  AD ) in 975  AD , and the royal families of South Tang were hunted down. Li Tianyi's son fled and changed the surname (Li) to Deng (鄧), his father's title."]}]},{"name":"Beemden","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English: (i) locative name from Beedon (Berks), Beadon (in Hennock, Devon), or Baydon (Wilts). (ii) locative name for someone who lived by the hill, from Middle English  <i>bi doun</i> (Old English, Middle English  <i>dūn</i> ‘hill’)."],"variants":[{"name":"Beedham","meanings":["1  English: (i) possibly from Bytham (Lincs), with Middle English lengthening and lowering of the main vowel to give modern  <i>Beedham</i>. (ii) Later forms of the name may have been confused with or represent   Beeden  .","2  English:  see  Beetham  ."]},{"name":"Bedden","meanings":["English: variant of   Beeden  ."]},{"name":"Beadon","meanings":["English:  see  Beeden  ."]},{"name":"Beedon","meanings":["English:  see  Beeden  ."]}]},{"name":"Adriane","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Modern feminine form of   Adrian  , less common than   Adrienne ."],"variants":[{"name":"Adrianna","meanings":["Modern feminine form of   Adrian  , less common than   Adrienne ."]},{"name":"Adriana","meanings":["From Latin.  See  <b>Adrian</b>   ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1356696,"age":6,"year":"1506","julianDay":2271115,"description":"The Netherlands is inherited by the future Habsburg Emperor and King of Spain Charles V.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1356697,"age":16,"year":"1516","julianDay":2274767,"description":"The Catholic King Charles I of Spain ruled the Netherlands.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Adriane Jansdr van den Beemden was born in 1500, in Breda, North Brabant, Netherlands, her father, Jan Willems Vanden Breemden, was 25 and her mother, Maria Adriaen Henric Eements Heems, was 20. She married Jan Mathijsz Peter Dirven in 1526. They were the parents of at least 3 sons and 3 daughters. She died in 1560, in her hometown, at the age of 60."},"et":{"1500–1560":"1500–1560","1490–1555":"1490–1555","1516–1591":"1516–1591","1533–Male":"1533–Surnud","1535–Male":"1535–Surnud","1537–Female":"1537–Surnud","1542–Male":"1542–Surnud","1475–Male":"1475–Surnud","1480–Female":"1480–Surnud","1560":"1560","1591":"1591","1480":"1480","1490":"1490","1535":"1535","1500":"1500","1533":"1533","1555":"1555","1542":"1542","1475":"1475","1506":"1506","1516":"1516","1526":"1526","1537":"1537","Breda, Breda, Noord-Brabant, Pays-Bas":"Breda, Noord-Brabant, Madalmaad","Netherlands":"Madalmaad","Poortugaal, South Holland, Netherlands":"Poortugaal, Zuid-Holland, Madalmaad","Breda, North Brabant, Netherlands":"Breda, Noord-Brabant, Madalmaad"},"fi":{"1500–1560":"1500–1560","1490–1555":"1490–1555","1516–1591